<FIRST>r a AM-NewspapersSold     08-23 0223</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Newspapers Sold,0228</SECOND>
<HEAD>MediaNews Group Buys Two Worrell Newspapers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MediaNews Group Inc. announced Tuesday it had
purchased two daily newspapers from Worrell Enterprises _ the
Potomac News in Woodbridge, Va., and the Las Cruces (N.M.) Sun News
_ for an undisclosed amount.
   MediaNews also said it had sold The Journal-News of Hamilton,
Ohio, to Thomson Newspapers for an undisclosed amount. The deal was
made by MediaNews subsidiary Garden State Newspapers.
   ``The transaction allows Garden State to enter two of the fastest
growing markets in the country,'' William Dean Singleton, the
company's co-owner, said. ``And it allows our Hamilton newspaper
under its new owner to benefit from the strong strategic position
held by Thomson in Ohio.''
   Houston-based MediaNews owns more than 20 daily newspapers,
including The Houston Post and The Denver Post, spokeswoman Pat
Robinson said. The company also owns more than 25 weekly newspapers.
   The Potomac News has a circulation of 25,000, while the Las
Cruces newspaper has a circulation of about 20,000, according to the
Audit Bureau of Circulation.
   Singleton said he planned no dramatic changes at either
newspaper. ``The management all stays the same. We'll add our little
touches here and there,'' he said.
   Garden State is owned by Singleton, MediaNews co-owner Richard B.
Scudder, and Media General Inc., the Richmond, Va., based company,
Ms. Robinson said.
</TEXT>
