<HEAD>Swedish Volvos may be Produced in South Korea</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Swedish Volvos would be produced in
South Korea under a contract being negotiated with Ssangyong Motor
Co., company officials said today.
   Under an agreement expected to be signed in September, Volvo
would initially supply the main components and parts for the
assembly of medium and large-size cars beginning in 1991, Ssangyong
said. Cars would be sold in the domestic market, it said.
   Ssangyong produces specially equipped vehicles, buses and jeeps
but has not entered the local car market. This would be the first
European brand car to be made and sold domestically.
   The Ministry of Trade and Industry confirmed today that Ssangyong
has filed papers outlining the venture. Further details were not
available.
