<HEAD>Former Governor Now Selling Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HENDERSON, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former Gov. Ray Blanton has taken a job
selling used cars and trucks.
   Blanton, who served two years in prison after leaving office,
said he has been in training for the job for about two weeks.
   ``I'm healthy as a horse, broke, but not broken,'' he said
Tuesday. Blanton has been working at Bolton Ford-Mercury for two
