<DATELINE>PARKIN, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   FBI agents arrested the mayor on cocaine
charges after a three-year investigation into local drug trafficking.
   Mayor Tommy Voyles, 43, was freed on $50,000 bond Tuesday after
appearing before a U.S. magistrate. The mayor, who was elected in
1986, made no comment as he was led in handcuffs into the federal
courthouse.
   ``It's just a tragedy. We hate to see drug-related accusations of
public corruption,'' U.S. Attorney Chuck Banks said.
