by a federal grand jury. The charges include one count of conspiring
to distribute cocaine and seven counts of cocaine distribution from
1987 though 1989, FBI spokesman Ron Wolfe said.
   A separate indictment charges that Voyles conspired to distribute
cocaine with William Criswell, 50, a used-car dealer, Wolfe said.
Criswell was released Tuesday on his own recognizance.
