<SECOND>AM-Tunisia-Rains,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rains Kill 10 in Tunisia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUNIS, Tunisia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rains in south and central Tunisia
left 10 people dead, the Tunisian Press Agency reported Wednesday.
   Five members of one family died near Sfax, a tourist resort on
the Mediterranean coast, when their vehicle was swept off the road
by waters spilling over the banks of a rain-swollen river, TAP
reported.
   At Kairouan, in central Tunisia, two people drowned in the rising
Nebhana River and lightning killed three others, the news agency
said.
   Kairouan authorities asked people living near rivers to move to
higher ground.
   Southern Tunisia, a desert region dotted with oases, experienced
heavy showers Tuesday night and Wednesday morning, but the northern
parts of the country, including the capital of Tunis, remained hot
and dry.
