<FIRST>r f PM-S&amp;L-Vento     08-23 0204</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-S&amp;L-Vento,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Vento To Head Task Force To Oversee S&amp;L Cleanup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Bruce F. Vento has been selected to head a
special savings and loan industry task force that will oversee the
newly established Resolution Trust Corp., a congressman said.
   Rep. Frank Annunzio, D-Ill., chairman of the House Banking,
Finance and Urban Affairs subcommittee on financial institutions
supervision, regulation and insurance, announced the appointment
Tuesday of Vento, D-Minn.
   The Resolution Trust Corp., which replaces the defunct Federal
Savings and Loan Insurance Corp., will take over and clean up
insolvent savings and loans and be responsible for the initial $50
billion to be used to merge or sell about 500 thrifts.
   The Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. will manage the Resolution
Trust Corp.
   Other Democrats named to the task force are Reps. John J. LaFalce
of New York, Mary Rose Oakar of Ohio, Charles E. Schumer of New
York, Barney Frank of Massachusetts, Paul E. Kanjorski of
Pennsylvania, Gerald D. Kleczka of Wisconsin, C. Thomas McMillen of
Maryland, Kweisi Mfume of Maryland and Jim McDermott of Washington.
   Annunzio said he has asked Rep. Chalmers P. Wylie of Ohio,
ranking Republican on the subcommittee, to name seven GOP members to
the task force.
</TEXT>
