<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     08-23 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Treasury Notes at Highest Level of Summer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 2-year Treasury notes rose in
Tuesday's auction to the highest level since May.
   The average yield was 8.37 percent, up from 7.75 percent at the
last comparable auction on July 26.
   It was the highest rate since 2-year notes averaged 8.84 percent
on May 24. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8\ percent
with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,978.30.
   A total of $9.50 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$24.02 billion.
</TEXT>
