<FIRST>u f PM-WangPresident     08-23 0214</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Wang President,0221</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wang Laboratories Names Richard W. Miller President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOWELL, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wang Laboratories Inc. has named the former
head of General Electric's consumer electronics business to the post
of president and chief operating officer, company officials
announced today.
   Richard W. Miller, 48, who has held several top operating and
chief executive officer positions and has led successful company
turnarounds, replaces Henry H.S. Chou.
   Chou served as acting president and chief operating officer since
the resignation of Frederick A. Wang, son of company founder and
Chairman An Wang, on Aug. 8.
   ``I have great confidence in the ability of Rick Miller to assume
total control of the operations of Wang Laboratories,'' said An
Wang, who also is the company's chief executive officer. ``He will
have my full support and that of the board of directors in resolving
the company's current situation and restoring it to profitability.''
   In an interview today in New York, Miller said he wants Wang
staffers to ``know where we're going, restore their dignity and give
them pride in the company's turnaround and accomplishments.''
   Miller also said it is ``quite likely'' the company will get an
infusion of new money by issuing more stock or debt or a
combination. He said there were no plans to sell Wang.
</TEXT>
