<FIRST>r f BC-AutoRecall     08-23 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Auto Recall,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ford Recalls 453,000 Fords and Mercurys</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. on Wednesday recalled about
453,000 1985-86 models of Ford and Mercury cars for an emission
control problem.
   The company said the cars emit too many hydrocarbons, an air
pollutant.
   Involved in the action are Ford Thunderbird, LTD and Mustang
models and Mercury Cougar, Marquis and Capri cars. All have
3.8-liter engines and automatic transmissions.
   Owners are being notified by mail and repairs will be performed
free of charge. The recall does not affect vehicles originally sold
in California or Canada.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
